  "reasons": "To find out how many miles Sophia can drive on a single tank of gas, we need to determine the number of miles she can drive per gallon of gas. We can do this by dividing the total number of miles she has traveled by the total number of gallons of gas she has used. Then, we can multiply this value by the number of gallons her tank can hold to find the total number of miles she can drive on a full tank. Based on the given information, Sophia has traveled 100 miles and needed 4 gallons of gas to fill up her tank. This gives us a rate of 100 miles / 4 gallons = 25 miles per gallon. Since her tank holds 12 gallons of gas, she can drive 25 miles per gallon * 12 gallons = 300 miles on a single tank of gas.",
